From: DozenOS autobuild <autobuild@dozenos.local>
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: use an absolute syscalltbl path for out-of-tree header gen

tools/lib/perf's `uapi-asm-generic` rule (tools/lib/perf/Makefile) invokes
scripts/Makefile.asm-headers to generate arm64's
arch/arm64/include/generated/uapi/asm/unistd_64.h. During the linux-perf
Debian package build (`make -C tools/perf install`, via the DozenOS
0002-build-linux-perf-package.patch), that sub-make runs with a working
directory that is NOT the kernel source root.

arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls overrides syscalltbl with a path that is
relative to the source root:

    syscalltbl = arch/arm64/tools/syscall_%.tbl

so the unistd header's prerequisite cannot be resolved from the perf build
directory and the build dies with:

    No rule to make target '.../unistd_64.h'.  Stop.
    make[8]: *** [Makefile:108: uapi-asm-generic] Error 2

Prefix it with $(srctree), exactly as the default in
scripts/Makefile.asm-headers does (syscalltbl := $(srctree)/scripts/syscall.tbl)
and as every non-overriding arch already gets. This is harmless for the
normal in-tree build, where srctree is the source root anyway, and it is why
x86 (which does not override syscalltbl) builds the linux-perf package fine.

Signed-off-by: DozenOS autobuild <autobuild@dozenos.local>
---
 arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls b/arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/Makefile.syscalls
@@ -3,4 +3,4 @@
 syscall_abis_32 +=
 syscall_abis_64 += renameat rlimit memfd_secret

-syscalltbl = arch/arm64/tools/syscall_%.tbl
+syscalltbl = $(srctree)/arch/arm64/tools/syscall_%.tbl
